%N A393487 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) (0 <= k <= n) giving binomial basis coefficients of excess-tail polynomials p_n(s) = Sum_{k=0..n} T(n,k)*binomial(s-2,k) for connected defect clusters in the row-word inversion statistic on standard Young tableaux of shape (m,m,m).
%C A393487 The excess-tail polynomial p_n(s) = d_s(n) counts connected defect cluster types at span s and excess n above the threshold weight 3s-2. These polynomials have degree n in s and admit the binomial decomposition p_n(s) = Sum_{k=0..n} T(n,k)*binomial(s-2,k).
%C A393487 Conjecture: the diagonal entries satisfy the factorization T(n,n-j) = 2^(n-2j) * Sum_{r=0..j} A393486(j,r)*binomial(n,r), where A393486(j,j) = 3^j. This has been verified numerically for j = 0..5.
%C A393487 Empirically, the cluster counts d_s(n) are polynomial in s of degree n for s sufficiently large (verified within the computed range).
%H A393487 Morten Brydensholt, <a href="/A393487/a393487.txt">Python program</a>
%F A393487 T(n,n) = 2^n (conjectured; verified for n = 0..10).
%F A393487 Conjecture: T(n,n-j) = 2^(n-2j) * Sum_{r=0..j} A393486(j,r)*binomial(n,r) (verified for j = 0..5).
%F A393487 Conjecture: the leading coefficient of p_n(s) is 2^n / n!.
